description:
Three people have died in Indonesia in a fire that was started during anti-government clashes. The blaze broke out at a regional parliament building in the country's east. Violence erupted after security forces killed a civilian at a protest on Friday. Demonstrators had been rallying against allowances for privileges for lawmakers.
